    metaDescription: 'Intelligence as a Service (IaaS) is the model where your IP becomes a persistent intelligence layer applied to client work. Learn how Client Intelligence is the platform built for it.',
    prose: 'Service businesses have always sold access to expertise. The traditional model is simple: clients hire experts for their time, the expert applies their knowledge, the client receives deliverables and advice. Time is the unit of exchange. Capacity is limited by how many hours the expert has.\n\nIntelligence as a Service (IaaS) is a different model. Instead of selling access to an expert\'s time, IaaS businesses deliver the expert\'s intelligence, their methodology, their Frameworks, their accumulated knowledge, systematically and at scale. The expert\'s thinking is encoded in AI systems that apply it consistently across clients, engagements, and deliverables. Time is no longer the bottleneck. Methodology is the asset.\n\nThis shift has fundamental implications for service business economics. In a time-based model, revenue scales linearly with hours. You serve more clients by working more hours or hiring more people. In an IaaS model, once your methodology is encoded, it applies across additional clients without proportional time investment. Revenue scales faster than headcount.\n\nIaaS also changes the value proposition to clients. Instead of buying hours and hoping they produce outcomes, clients buy systematic application of proven methodology. The deliverables are consistent regardless of which team member handles the account, which day of the week it is, or how busy the consultant is. Clients who understand IaaS often prefer it to traditional models because the consistency and methodology-fidelity are higher.\n\nClient Intelligence is purpose-built for IaaS businesses. The Account Brain is where your methodology lives. Client Workspaces are where it gets applied at scale. The 27 Intelligence Mode tools and 16 action and output skills are the delivery layer. The result: a service business where your intelligence is the product, not your time, and where growth does not require proportional expansion of your personal working hours.',
